An MP yesterday asked the Ministry of Education to amend laws of appointing university vice chancellors for qualified non-locals to head the institutions.Matayos MP Geoffrey Odanga said having new rules barring appointment of professionals from the university s locality will cure ethnic conflicts. He challenged Education CS Fred Matiang i to come up with laws to help diversify leadership of institutions to assist the country realise national integration. Education is the only thing that has over the years united Kenyans. University vice chancellors should not serve in the region they were born, Odanga said.Last week, Uasin Gishu Governor Jackson Mandako, his Elgeyo Marakwet counterpart Alex Tolgos and MPs Oscar Sudi (Kapseret), Sila Tiren (Moiben) and James Bett (Kesses) stormed the Moi University.They were protesting against the appointment of Prof Laban Ayiro as the acting VC.